!!!LUCKY NUMBER 7!!!
-----

Setup:
   Edit a configuration file in the style of cfg_example.yml. The necessary variables
   to set are:
      1. dir - Absolute path to the directory containing lab4. Scripts have access to dir/R/.
      2. data - Absolute path to the directory containing image{1..3}.txt. Example scripts
            will not try to access files with any different numbers.
   REQUIRED LIBRARIES:
      yaml
      optparse
      dplyr
      reshape2
      ggplot2
      MASS
      Rcpp

Example Scripts:
   Running example scripts:
      To run an example script, manually supply the variable args$config to point to the
      appropriate .yml file, or else run the script with the (-c) argument to set the 
      args$config variable at runtime.
   Use any of the example scripts:
      1. elcm_example.R - ???
      2. crf_example.R - ???
      3. ising_example.R - ???
